<LP>
   NEW YORK -- General Instrument Corp. said it plans to sell
its transportation electronics division as part of a
restructuring and debt-reduction plan.
   In the year ended Feb. 28, the division had sales of about
$40 million. It makes automotive electronic displays. General
Instrument was recently acquired by an investor group led by
Forstmann, Little &amp; Co.
